[SN]TITLE[SN]
Didcot murders: Suspect scrawled 'I'm sorry' on walls

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A suspected triple murderer wrote "I'm sorry" on the wall of the house where his mother and half-sister were found dead, an inquest has heard.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police believe Jed Allen, 21, killed Janet Jordon, 48, her daughter Derrin, six, and her partner Philip Howard, 44, in a "violent" hunting knife attack.
Their bodies were found at their home in Didcot, Oxfordshire, in May, while Allen was found dead two days later.
Coroner Darren Salter recorded a verdict of unlawful killing.
